bilingual.target: 妈妈手指，妈妈手指，你在哪里？

bilingual.source: I cut my finger while I was chopping onions.
bilingual.target: 我切洋葱时割到了手指。

bilingual.source: Although he had broken his finger, he continued his circus act.
bilingual.target: 尽管他手指骨折了，他还是继续他的马戏表演。

bilingual.source: Franklin then touched the key with his finger and got an electric shock.
bilingual.target: 富兰克林用手指触摸钥匙，结果被电击了。

list.abstract: Finger（英 [ˈfɪŋɡə]，美 [ˈfɪŋɡər]），英语单词，作名词时为手指；指状物。作动词为用手指触摸；向警方告发；用某种指法演奏。例句：Sophie's mother's finger was cut by a knife.（苏菲的妈妈的手指被刀子割破了。）。
《Finger》是由郑址宇执导，韩智婉编剧，金秀贤主演的电视剧。

yingyinNormal.en: Pull my finger. My hand is messed up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拉我的手指，我的手毁了。

yingyinNormal.en: You may want to lose the foam finger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不把这个泡沫大手指扔掉么？

yingyinNormal.en: Really? Who has seen the "Charlie bit my finger." "Charlie bit my finger. He bit my finger, Charlie." Oh, Charlie.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真的吗？谁看过查理咬了我的手指头。查理咬了我的手指头。他咬了我的手指头，查理。噢，查理。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, put your finger on it. Doesn't matter which finger. Good choice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在，把你的手指放上去，无所谓用哪根手指，明智的选择。

yingyinNormal.en: Damn it! I cut my finger! Happy Halloween. No, really, I cut myself. Look!
yingyinNormal.zh: 该死，我切到我的手指了。万圣节快乐。我是说真的，我切到手指了，你看！

yingyinNormal.en: Little finger sandwiches, too. This place is amazing. Interesting thing about finger sandwiches: you put enough of them together, you got a sandwich.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有手指三明治 这地方棒极了。手指三明治有意思的是：你把足够分量拼起来，就能得到一个完整的三明治。

yingyinNormal.en: Do I have your blessing? Well, Sheldon, I think you should make her finger like Saturn and put a ring on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你会祝福我吗？谢尔顿...我觉得你应该将她的手指变成土星再往她手指上套个土星"环"。

yingyinNormal.en: The crab is pinching Grandpa Pig's finger. Ouch. Naughty, Mr. Crab.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这只螃蟹钳住爷爷的手指了。好疼。真是调皮的螃蟹。

yingyinNormal.en: Baby-proofing a guillotine? So you cut your finger off. It's part of the fun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 给断头台做防护？你把手指切断，这才是有趣啊。

yingyinNormal.en: And here we have a waitress brushing her teeth with her finger. AKA you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而这是一位女招待，只会用手指抠牙齿而已，确切来说就是你。

yingyinNormal.en: I just have to get to Kai, grab his finger, and then, Skadoosh. Back to the Spirit Realm.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只需要找到天煞，捏住他的手指，然后，走你，他就能滚回灵界。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. It's a front-projected holographic display combined with laser-based finger tracking. Here, I'll show you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，这是正投影全息显示加上手指激光跟踪器，来，我给你演示。

yingyinNormal.en: You didn't lift a finger. No, but I narrated the entire event, and I am paying for it today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你昨天手指都没抬一下。是没有，但我为整个活动做了旁白，而今天我就得忍受那酸痛。

yingyinNormal.en: Except for a short time when Comanches cut off my great-great-great-grandmother's finger and stole it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除了中间有一小段时间，印第安人把我曾曾曾祖母的手指切下来，把戒指偷走。

yingyinNormal.en: And what are you, widowed or divorced? Wedding ring is at least 30 years old and you've moved it to another finger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是寡妇还是离婚了？婚戒至少30年了，而你改用另一根手指戴了。

yingyinNormal.en: All right. All right. Maybe it will take my mind off it. You promise to buy me a big foam finger? You got it. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，或许能让我忘记伤痛，但你要帮我买个泡沫塑料做的大手指。一定。

yingyinNormal.en: And then just pick it with your finger, and if it's really al dente you'll still see a slight give in the middle. That's good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 用你的手指攥着它，如果捏起来很有劲道而中间还有一点弹性，那就可以了。

yingyinNormal.en: All right fine. Fine, I'll do it. I've just got to get this off the screen. Carol and Susan are still upset that you taught him pull my finger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，让我来，我们得把这个消掉，卡萝还在气你教他“拉我的手指”。

yingyinNormal.en: I think the one thing where I kind of lost it a little bit, He'd come down, he kind of like stutter-stepped, and spun And finger-rolled it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我记最让我激动不已的是，看着他带球，突然急停转身手指很柔软地轻轻一投

yingyinNormal.en: I'm using benefit's WATTS UP. And I apply this highest portion up my cheek and then I'm gonna blend it with my finger.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我用的是benefit's的WATTS UP，我把最大的量涂在脸颊上，然后用手指涂抹匀。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃饭时，男人的结婚戒指从手指上滑落。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数数字系统是两个因素的副产品：人类的语言能力和专注于手和手指的倾向。

examination_example.sentence: Our ancestors' hands served as the gateway to the realization that "five <highlight>fingers</highlight> in one is the same as five <highlight>fingers</highlight> on the other."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们祖先的手是通向“一个手指上的五个手指和另一个手指上的五个手指是一样的”这一认识的大门。
